      <notesStmt>
        <note>Title from colophon. Cover folio reads: atha kālabhairavasahasranāma. Title from f. 2v is Bhairavastavarāja.</note>
        <note>Cataloged by Poleman as Bhairavasahasranāmastotra in the Umāmaheśvarasaṁvāda.</note>
        <note>Written 9 lines per leaf.</note>
        <note>Good condition. Mistakes covered over with white. Orange powder rubbed in over invocation, colophon, some words and all numbers. Marginal corrections.</note>
        <note>Written on European paper with watermarks. Ff. 1-11 blue paper, ff. 12-13 light aqua. Watermarks, ff. 2, 6, and 7, have "London" written in center, above which "Millington" is written.</note>
        <note>Begins (f. 1v): śrīgaṇeśāya namaḥ. om̐. de. kailāsaśikhare ramye devadevaṁ jagadguruṁ papracha pārvatī kāntaṁ śaṅkaraṁ lokanāyakaṁ (verse 1). pārvatyuvāca. devadeva mahādeva sarvajña sukhadāyaka āpaduḥkhadaridrādipīḍitānāṁ nṛṇāṁ vibho (verse 2). yad vittaṁ sukhasaṁpattir dhanadhānyakaraṁ sadā viśeṣato rājakule śāntipuṣṭipradāyakaṁ (verse 3).</note>
        <note>Ends (f. 13r-v): satkulīnāya śāntāya ṛṣaye satyavādina stotradānāt suprahṛṣṭo bhairavobhūnmaheśvaraḥ (verse [1]72).</note>
        <note>Colophon (f. 13v): 1001 iti śrī uḍḍāmare tantre umāmaheśvarasaṁvāde bhairavasahasranāmastotraṁ sampūrṇaṁ.</note>
        <note>Text continues after colophon: atha bhairavamānasapūjā rudrayāmale kulacūḍāmaṇau. ādhāro bhujagādhirājava[l?]ayaṁ pātraṁ mahīmaṇḍalaṁ madyaṁ saptasamudravāripiśitaṁ cāṣṭau ca digdantinaḥ. so[']haṁ bhairavam arcayetpratidinaṁ tārāṁ gaṇair akṣitair ādityādinavagrahaiśca kusumair iṣṭārthasaṁsiddhaye (verse 1).</note>
      </notesStmt>
